explanation: This solution uses a single pass through the string to count the number of opening and closing parentheses. It keeps track of the number of opening parentheses that do not have a corresponding closing parenthesis and the number of closing parentheses that do not have a corresponding opening parenthesis. The minimum number of moves required to make the string valid is the sum of these two counts. This approach has a high efficiency due to its linear time complexity and constant space complexity.

